-- Egypt pound weakens on official, black market
-- By Shadia Nasralla
-- Mon May 05, 2014 06:40AM EDT
-- None



CAIRO, May 5 (Reuters) - The Egyptian pound weakened at a seventh central bank dollar sale <CBEO> in a row on Monday, with two Cairo-based forex traders saying it was the weakest rate since July when the army deposed Islamist President Mohamed Mursi.

